Iavan Pijoos, News24Pretoria - A man was killed when he was struck by a minibus taxi in central Pretoria on Thursday morning, paramedics said. The minibus struck another car before knocking the 42-year-old man down at the corner of Bloed and Lillian Ngoyi streets around 07:30, Netcare 911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said. The cause of the accident was not yet known. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.